  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Liberia: Strengthening the Rule of Law: Justice and Security for the Liberian People</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SGBV victims and survivors; justice sector actors, such as police, prosecutors, case liaison officers, victim support officers, public defenders and court staff from both the Nimba and Montserrado Sexual Offence Courts; clerks, bailiffs and recorders from Nimba, Lofa and Bong Counties; Women&#x2019;s and Children&#x2019;s Protection Section (WACPS) officers; nurses.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to strengthen the capacity of justice actors engaged in the investigation of sexual and gender-based violence (SGBV) on crime scene investigation, trial techniques and psycho-social counselling related to SGBV; enhance the efficiency, transparency and accountability of the specialized sexual offences courts in the Montserrado and Nimba counties; and ensure that survivors of SGBV and the more vulnerable have an increased understanding of the SGBV referral pathway and preventive mechanisms.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen the institutional capacity of the SGBV mechanisms at the national and local levels to respond to incidence of SGBV and ensure access to justice for survivors of SGBV.</narrative>
  </description>
